// Delete records individually throgh API access -> driver of the database.


MongoDB -> mongo -> queries (certain syntax way of extracting data) -> database engine (it makes sense of where the data you want is stored on the disk) -> sends you relevant data back.


// SQL v/s NoSQL

SQL = Structured Querying Language
SQL : Stored in RDBMS format(tables, rows, columns)
Database Engine = what data you want throgh SQL
This format is vertically scalable


NoSQL = It is usually NOT RDBMS
NoSQL : {"key": "value", "key2": 2}
They are horizontally scalable


Database
Collection(s)
Conllection -> Document(s)
Document -> JSON-like structure -> Key-Value pairs


// What is Mongoose
Sits on top of mongodb native driver(mongodb)

